            <!-- Main Content -->
            <div class="col-lg-9">
                <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm rounded-3">
                    <div class="card-body p-4">
                        <h3 class="card-title fw-bold mb-3 border-bottom pb-3"><%- title %></h3>
                
                        <p>At Pethudl, we value your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your data when you use our pet social media and marketplace platform.</p>
                        
                        <h5 class="mt-4 fw-semibold">1. Information We Collect</h5>
                        <p><strong>Personal Information:</strong> When you create an account, we collect your name, email address, phone number, and location. For marketplace transactions, we may collect payment information and shipping addresses.</p>
                        <p><strong>Pet Information:</strong> You may provide details about your pets including photos, breed, age, health records, and behavioral information for social sharing and marketplace listings.</p>
                        <p><strong>Usage Data:</strong> We automatically collect information about how you interact with Pethudl, including posts you view, searches you make, and features you use.</p>
                        
                        <h5 class="mt-4 fw-semibold">2. How We Use Your Information</h5>
                        <p>We use your information to provide and improve our services, including connecting pet owners, facilitating marketplace transactions, personalizing your feed, sending notifications about your pets and community, and ensuring platform safety and security.</p>
                        
                        <h5 class="mt-4 fw-semibold">3. Information Sharing</h5>
                        <p>We do not sell your personal information. We may share information with other Pethudl users as part of social features, with service providers who help operate our platform, with veterinarians or pet services you choose to connect with, and when required by law or to protect our users' safety.</p>
                        
                        <h5 class="mt-4 fw-semibold">4. Data Security</h5>
                        <p>We implement appropriate security measures to protect your information, including encryption, secure servers, and regular security audits. However, no internet transmission is completely secure.</p>
                        
                        <h5 class="mt-4 fw-semibold">5. Your Rights and Choices</h5>
                        <p>You can access, update, or delete your account information at any time through your profile settings. You may control who can see your pet profiles and posts, opt out of certain communications, and request data portability or account deletion.</p>
                        
                        <h5 class="mt-4 fw-semibold">6. Children's Privacy</h5>
                        <p>Pethudl is intended for users 13 years and older. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe we have collected such information, please contact us immediately.</p>
                        
                        <h5 class="mt-4 fw-semibold">7. Cookies and Tracking</h5>
                        <p>We use cookies and similar technologies to enhance your experience, remember your preferences, and analyze site usage. You can control cookie settings through your browser.</p>
                        
                        <h5 class="mt-4 fw-semibold">8. Third-Party Services</h5>
                        <p>Pethudl may integrate with third-party services like payment processors, mapping services, or veterinary platforms. These services have their own privacy policies that govern their use of your information.</p>
                        
                        <h5 class="mt-4 fw-semibold">9. Data Retention</h5>
                        <p>We retain your information for as long as your account is active or as needed to provide services. Some information may be retained longer for legal or safety purposes.</p>
                        
                        <h5 class="mt-4 fw-semibold">10. International Users</h5>
                        <p>If you access Pethudl from outside our primary jurisdiction, your information may be transferred and processed in countries with different privacy laws.</p>
                        
                        <h5 class="mt-4 fw-semibold">11. Changes to This Policy</h5>
                        <p>We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. We will notify you of significant changes through email or platform notifications.</p>
                        
                        <p class="mt-4">For privacy-related questions or concerns, contact us at <a href="mailto:privacy@Pethudl.com">privacy@Pethudl.com</a>.</p>
                        
                        <p class="mt-3 text-muted"><em>Last updated: September 6, 2025</em></p>
